## Strategic context — solutions architecture

This project was evaluated today against three professional frameworks:

**Forward Deployed Engineering** — embedding in a real operational environment, identifying where technology solves real problems, building solutions directly in context. This project is a textbook FDE example — built from inside a real incident, on the day it occurred.

**Legal Operations** — reducing attorney time on non-billable operational confusion, building scalable knowledge systems, reducing risk from information gaps. This is the entire legal ops mandate.

**Solutions Architecture** — designing technically sound systems that solve domain-specific problems at scale. The three-layer architecture, PostgreSQL with JSONB, pseudonymization pattern, append-only audit trail — these are SA-level decisions.

**The combination of all three is the rare thing.** Most people in these roles do one well. The ceiling in solutions architecture is higher because the same system design can be deployed across many firms, many industries, and many contexts. The domain knowledge built here becomes more valuable at every step.

**Demo target:** 200-300 incidents by end of year from daily practice. Enough to produce confident judge profiles, meaningful eCourts reliability flags, and IF/THEN rules with high confidence scores backed by repeated confirmation. A demo with 8 months of real operational data is significantly stronger than one with synthetic examples.

